<font color="#FF0000">PRIORITIES</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug  4  9:46:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I actually know what Lisa is talking about.  You think you are in love because your insides hurt when you can't see this person on a certain day.  But then it dawns on you that you are spending more of your time thinking about him and what he needs than yourself.  It only comes in splinters when you are willing to face the fact that you are not all that happy.  Any relationship I think is give and take and someone shouldn't have control over what you do and who you are. For a while you might think that this shows that he cares but it can get really tiring.  I think that your priorities in a relationship should be honesty -- someone who takes you for what you are.
